<item>
            <title>[SPARK-35027] Close the inputStream in FileAppender when writing the logs failure</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-35027</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In Spark Cluster, the&#160;ExecutorRunner uses&#160;FileAppender&#160; to redirect the stdout/stderr of executors to file, when the writing processing is failure due to some reasons: disk full, the FileAppender will only close the input stream to file, but leave the pipe&apos;s stdout/stderr open, following writting operation in executor side may be hung.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;need to close the inputStream in FileAppender ?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13371210">SPARK-35027</key>
            <summary>Close the inputStream in FileAppender when writing the logs failure</summary>
