                            <comment id="17330976" author="srowen" created="Fri, 23 Apr 2021 18:23:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Are you sure? stop() is called on an error on these FileAppenders.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17372425" author="jhu" created="Thu, 1 Jul 2021 06:34:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Of course, the &quot;stop&quot; in FileAppender does nothing but set a flag.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The exception will be thrown in &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/util/logging/FileAppender.scala#L59&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;appendStreamToFile&lt;/a&gt;&quot;, but the cloure in finally only closes the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/util/logging/FileAppender.scala#L79&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;output stream (to file)&lt;/a&gt;, but leave the &quot;inputStream&quot; open., which is the pipe&apos;s output stream.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17377257" author="apachespark" created="Thu, 8 Jul 2021 09:31:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;jhu-chang&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
